30|$|Our goal in {{this section}} is to study the {{asymptotical}} behavior of {{the solution to the}} Dirichlet problem of the modified Helmholtz equation, as the frequency, or, equivalently, the wavenumber, approaches infinity. This large-β asymptotic analysis will be based on the integral representation (2.3), and it will be carried out by using the <b>method</b> <b>of</b> <b>steepest</b> <b>descents.</b>|$|R
30|$|Based on the {{integral}} {{representations of the}} solution derived via Fokas’ transform method, the high-frequency asymptotics for {{the solution of the}} modified Helmholtz equation, in a half-plane and subject to the Dirichlet condition, is discussed. For the case of piecewise constant boundary data, full asymptotic expansions of the solution are obtained by using Watson’s lemma and the <b>method</b> <b>of</b> <b>steepest</b> <b>descents</b> for definite integrals.|$|R
